    <article id="about-article">
     <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
       <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-6 col-lg-6">
        <h1 class="ttl-sctn">
         About Us
        </h1>
        <p class="rd-txt">
         Camping Castel San Pietro is enclosed in a natural oasis within the ancient city wall of the city of Verona. The city, an UNESCO World Heritage Site, is located in a convenient climatic and geographic position that made it an important crossroad for arts and culture for more than two millennia.
 On a hill of the city, directly facing the city center and surrounded by a botanic garden, the camping offers a relaxing and enjoyable environment for its guests.
 Accommodation fees include camping pitches for tents, and parking spaces for campers and caravans. All the location are uniquely characterized in order to meet different guest needs.
 Caravans and tents can also be rented by the people who don’t carry the equipment but want to enjoy a green and relaxing stay a few minutes walk away from the city center.
 The camping, in fact, is a convenient resting point for cyclist that are traveling around the province of Verona. By in advance reservation, the camping can also accommodate groups of students accompanied by their teachers or other chaperones.
        </p>
        <div class="embed-container">
         <iframe allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Zqd2GOK803U?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0" width="560">
         </iframe>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-6 col-lg-6">
        <h1 class="ttl-sctn">
         Where we are
        </h1>
        <p class="rd-txt">
        </p>
        <p class="rd-txt">
         <b>
          Address:
         </b>
         Via Castel San Pietro 2, 37129, Verona
